				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{{\mathrm{V}}}}_{{{\mathrm{O}}}}^ +$$\end{document} signal)32. We have observed the Signal 3 (g = 2.0027 ± 0.0002) in the ESR measurements of both ZnO/PC61BM and ZnO/PC71BM films (Supplementary Fig. 3). Therefore, the Signal 2 and Signal 3 are identified as the PC61BM anion signal and the hole signal of ZnO (VO+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
