The transient responses of the Nspin of the Signal 1, Signal 2, and Signal 3 upon solar irradiation are shown by Green rhombus, orange triangles, and purple squares in Fig. 7a, b, respectively. The total Nspin corresponds to the sum of these three components. The Nspin for the Signal 1, Signal 2, and Signal 3 were calculated by the deconvolution of the ESR signals by the fitting analyzes shown in Fig. 6. The Nspin of the Signal 2 dominates the total Nspin. The Nspin of the Signal 3 shows the similar transient response regardless of with or without ITIC (Fig. 7a, b). However, the Nspin for the Signal 1 and Signal 2 for the cell with ITIC are obviously smaller than those of the cell without ITIC (Fig. 7a, b). The transient responses of the relative open-circuit voltage (VOC(t)/VOC(0)) and the Nspin in the high magnetic fields at around 327.5 mT obtained from the cells with and without ITIC are shown in Fig. 7c, d, respectively, where VOC(t) is normalized to the initial value of VOC(0) at t = 0. For this case, we observe another correlation between the increase in VOC(t)/VOC(0) and the decrease in the Nspin of the Signal 4 (hole signal of ZnO (Zni+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
